    diagnostics: ["Antisynthetase antibody panel: anti-Jo-1 (most common, 60-80% of cases), anti-PL-7, anti-PL-12, anti-EJ, anti-OJ, anti-KS","Serum creatine kinase (CK): elevated 5-50x upper limit of normal in active myositis; may be normal in ILD-predominant disease","High-resolution CT (HRCT) chest: bilateral ground-glass opacities (NSIP pattern) or consolidation (organizing pneumonia pattern)","Pulmonary function tests (PFTs): restrictive pattern with reduced FVC and DLCO; DLCO is the most sensitive early parameter","Muscle MRI (STIR sequences): edema in proximal muscle groups identifies active myositis and guides biopsy","Muscle biopsy: perimysial inflammation with perifascicular necrosis distinguishing from other inflammatory myopathies"],
